  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "u85XNE91RrZoVa73GL0exEt6dgI=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:36.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## The next track\n\nLive collaboration via ACT + GSOC is the remaining major track on the chat roadmap as of 2026-04-18. Detailed plan in `live-collaboration-design.md`.\n\n## What \"live\" means\n\nBoth users have the document open. When one commits an op, the other sees it appear in the **toolbar's History view within a second or two**, attributed to the correct signer.\n\n## Explicit non-goals\n\n- **No cursor overlays.**\n- **No caret labels.**\n- **No per-editor presence.**\n\nPowerhouse editors are too varied -- tables, visual canvases, dashboards, button grids -- for any of that to be meaningful across the surface.\n\n## Supporting foundation\n\nSignatures are already preserved end-to-end (shipped 2026-04-17), so the toolbar history shows the real author of every revision as soon as the pull mechanism lands. That's what makes attribution in live collab trivially correct.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:36.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:36.000Z"
    }
  },
